# Article 5 — The Schism
## What the AP Counts Tell You About the Break, and Why the Numbers Are Still Talking

Every negotiated settlement leaves a record. In conventional commercial disputes, that record is a contract — signed, witnessed, filed. In the Banksy enterprise's settlement, the record is an edition structure. The AP counts on the post-schism prints are the contract. The colorway allocations are the annexures. The works that carry no AP at all are the clauses that were never agreed.

This is not a metaphor. The enterprise encoded its ownership structure into its production arithmetic from the beginning — the twenty-two AP baseline that resolves into one artist copy, ten VIP allocation units, eleven POW retained inventory — and it continued encoding that structure through the schism and its aftermath. The edition numbers on the prints produced after 2005 are the forensic record of a renegotiation. You can read the terms of the settlement by counting the APs.

---

The schism's root is Hirst's 2009 decision. He abandons the multi-artist diversification plan — the arrangement under which the enterprise would have expanded into a stable of artists, with Banksy as the flagship but not the monopoly. He goes all-in on himself and Banksy instead, breaking the artist's walk-away deal and triggering the sequence of events the corporate record documents. The LA print run violation follows: POW pushes commercial prints into the public domain without the artist's sign-off on the quality terms embedded in her deal. The final-say clause is breached. The artist withdraws.

But the schism does not arrive fully formed in 2009. It begins earlier, in the edition structures. The Barely Legal prints of 2005 — all six carrying a uniform AP count of six — are the first legible marker of a changed relationship between the artist and the enterprise's commercial apparatus. Six is not a multiple of twenty-two. Six is the AP structure of a print where the standard allocation has been reduced to its minimum viable form: one for the artist, one for the AoR, one for POW, and three for the VIP tier at half the standard rate. The uniformity of AP=6 across all six LA prints is the edition-level signal that the artist is already operating at arm's length from the standard commercial allocation before the LA print run violation makes the breach explicit.

---

Warren is fired in 2006. Warren is the artist's front person at POW — the operational intermediary between the artist's production and the commercial apparatus — and the Santa's Ghetto 2006 debacle is the documented occasion. Eine is fired in the same period, following the eBay backdoor print scandal. Eine sold unauthorised prints through a private channel, violating the distribution protocols that made the authentication architecture function. Two personnel actions, one window. The enterprise's disciplinary mechanism activating against the people closest to the artist's direct operational involvement.

The aftermath is Lazarides' buyout in October 2008 — the financial mechanism of the broader separation — and Durban's resignation from LazInc in March 2009, the administrative confirmation that closes the account. The schism's personnel record runs from Warren's firing in 2006 to Durban's LazInc departure in March 2009. Three years. Three acts. The edition structures record each of them.

---

The post-schism signed prints are where the renegotiation becomes legible most directly.

Control Your Weapon and NOLA Girl — the signed colorway editions produced in the post-schism period — carry Hirst's signature as AoR. Not the artist's. The AoR's. The schism renegotiation establishes that going forward, on the prints where the artist is not certifying her own involvement, the AoR signs. The artist made him sign on specific prints so that his signature would hang himself. Not figuratively. A signature by the AoR on a Banksy print is a public record of the AoR's role in the work's production and certification. The prints that carry Hirst's signature are the prints where the enterprise is operating without the artist's hand — and his signature is the proof, embedded in the object itself.

---

The NAPALM/SERPENTINE box set resolves the schism's most precise structural statement.

Fifty prints in the edition. Twenty-nine artist's proofs. Twenty-nine does not divide by twenty-two. It resolves by subtraction: the standard allocation minus the AoR's expected share, if the AoR is excluded from the AP tier as a condition of the artist's participation in a production associated with his institutional commemoration. Twenty-nine only makes sense with Hirst outside the fifty.

The Wreck of the Unbelievable edition-of-two with five APs is the obverse. An edition of two with five APs is structurally anomalous under normal commercial logic — you do not produce more artist's proofs than there are works in the edition. But if the five APs encode the artist's participation in a project whose edition is presented as Hirst's — one artist's copy per edition work, plus three additional APs encoding the artist's share of the Hirst commercial vehicle's proceeds — the five resolves as a contractual statement rather than a production anomaly. The edition-of-two is Hirst's. The five APs are the artist's share, encoded into the object because the object is where the enterprise put its contracts.

---

King Robbo in 2011 is the market's verdict on the enterprise without its artist.

The feud becomes in 2011 a commercial test of whether the enterprise can sustain the Banksy brand's cultural authority without the hand that built it. The answer is no. King Robbo is a commercial and critical failure. The enterprise discovers, with full market data, that the artist is necessary — that the brand's value is inseparable from the quality of the production, and the quality of the production is inseparable from the person who produces it.

The re-engagement comes in 2012. Evil Under the Sun for the Fiorucci Foundation. The conditions are a new capitalisation round — Round 2, funded by a new syndicate at terms that reflect the artist's demonstrated necessity and the enterprise's demonstrated vulnerability. The round funds Dismaland in 2015, the Walled Off Hotel in 2017, and Hirst's Wreck of the Unbelievable. The AP structures on the post-re-engagement prints are different from the pre-schism baseline. The renegotiation is in the numbers, as the original deal was in the numbers, as every subsequent amendment has been in the numbers.

---

The schism is not a falling-out. It is a contractual breach with a renegotiated settlement whose terms are encoded in the edition structures of every print produced during and after it.

The front-end marker is the Barely Legal AP=6 uniformity in 2005. The breach is the LA print run violation and the Warren/Eine firings of 2006. The financial mechanism is the Lazarides buyout in October 2008. The administrative confirmation is Durban's LazInc departure in March 2009. The market verdict is King Robbo in 2011. The settlement is Round 2 in 2012.

The edition arithmetic records each of these events without narrating them. Twenty-two becomes six. Six becomes an absence. The absence becomes Hirst's signature. Hirst's signature becomes twenty-nine. Twenty-nine becomes the re-engagement. The re-engagement becomes Dismaland, and the Walled Off Hotel, and the Wreck of the Unbelievable with its impossible five APs encoding the artist's share in the AoR's commemorative edition.

The numbers were not hiding. They were in the public record from the beginning, waiting for someone to read them in sequence.

